I"<h3 id="why-associations">Why Associations?</h3>

<p>Why do we need associations between models? Because they make common operations simpler and easier in your code.</p>

<p><strong>example:</strong></p>

<p>without association:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">@order = Order.create(:order_date =&gt; Time.now, :customer_id =&gt; @customer.id)</code></p>

<p>with association:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">@order= @customer.orders.create(:order_date=&gt; Time.now)</code></p>
:ET